      <h1>PRIVACY POLICY </h1>
      <p><strong>Last update 08 June 2018</strong></p>
      <p>Banuba Limited, having its registered address at Office A, 16/F Heng Shan Centre 145 Queen’s Road East, Wan Chai, Hong Kong, reg. No. 2360577 (hereinafter – <strong>Banuba Limited</strong>), together with companies in the same corporate group, take your privacy very seriously. Please, read carefully this following document to find about our Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy sets out our data processing practices and your options regarding the ways in which your personal information is used.</p>
      <h2>1. TERMS AND DEFINITIONS</h2>
      <p>The following terms used in this Privacy Policy shall have the following definitions: </p>
      <ul class="styled">
        <li><strong>"You"</strong> and <strong>"Your"</strong> relates to you, the user of Easy Snap App;</li>
        <li><strong>"We"</strong>, <strong>"Our"</strong> and <strong>"Us"</strong> relates to Banuba Limited and the companies in the same corporate group;</li>
        <li><strong>"Easy Snap App"</strong> - means Easy Snap mobile app which enables people to create photos and videos using filters and video effects;</li>
        <li><strong>"Services"</strong> - services of Easy Snap App.</li>
        <li><strong>“Information”</strong> - both personal and non-personal information.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>2. SCOPE OF APPLICATION </h2>
      <p>This Privacy Policy applies to the Services.</p>
      <h2>3. ACCEPTANCE OF THIS PRIVACY POLICY </h2>
      <p>By using the Services You express Your acceptance of this Privacy Policy, as such Policy may be amended from time to time. Each time You use the Services, You agree and expressly consent to Our collection, use, storage, transfer and disclosure of the information that You provide as described in this Policy. If You do not agree to be bound by this Privacy Policy then, please, do not use the Services.</p>
      <p>In addition to this Privacy Policy, please review Our Terms and Conditions available at <a href="https://www.banuba.com/easysnap/terms" target="_blank">https://www.banuba.com/easysnap/terms</a> and any other rules, policies and terms and conditions relating to the Services as notified to You by Us from time to time.</p>
      <h2>4. INFORMATION WE COLLECT</h2>
      <p><strong>Personal Information</strong></p>
      <p>For the purposes of this Privacy Policy personal information means information about You that is personally identifiable and includes Your name, address, date of birth, nationality, marital status, phone number, email address, or other information that is not otherwise publicly available and that is protected from disclosure under applicable laws.</p>
      <p>When You install Easy Snap App, You will not be asked to provide Us with Your phone number, name and/or photo. </p>
      <p>Easy Snap App does not intend to collect names, emails, addresses or other contact information from its users' mobile address book or contact lists.</p>
      <p>We do not intend to collect, use, process, store, share any of Your personal information. However, if such information may be collected along with other information, We may collect, it will be subject to restrictions, stipulated in section 5.</p>
      <p>We may collect the content and other information You provide to Us when You use Easy Snap App and content that You create or provide through Easy Snap App, including photos or videos. We may also collect information about Your activity when using Easy Snap App. </p>
      <p>We may collect Your photos and videos and use them for Our algorithms learning in order to provide You with best facial recognition experience. We will collect user’s photos and videos separately from names, so it will be not possible to identify the user.</p>
      <p>In case the applicable law stipulates that user’s photo and/or face geometry is considered as biometric identifier or biometric information or similar legal category, hereby You express Your informed written consent on such collection and use, as described in this Policy.</p>
      <p>We shall use and disclose Your personal information solely for the purposes stipulated in Sections 5 and 6.</p>
      <p>Upon receipt of Your written request and enough information to permit Us to identify Your personal information, We will disclose to You the personal information We hold about You. Upon Your request We will also rectify any personal information concerning You that is inaccurate.</p>
      <p><strong>Non-Personal Information</strong></p>
      <p>We also collect data in a form that does not, on its own, permit direct association with any specific individual (non-personal information). In particular, We may collect information from or about the Device, such as the operating system, IP address, device identifier and settings, cookie information, advertising identifier, unique application identifiers, browser type, language, wireless network, mobile network information, software and hardware attributes, as well as information about Your location. We may also collect information about Your activity when using the Services (including access time, pages viewed and other details of Your visits). All the mentioned information shall be collected, stored and processed purely in anonymized form. </p>
      <p>We may collect, use, transfer, and disclose Your non-personal information for any legal purpose, going beyond the purposes listed in Sections 5 and 6. In particular, We may share Your non-personal information with advertising companies for the purposes of delivering targeted advertisement on Our behalf, including on third-parties’ websites and apps.</p>
      <p>If We do combine non-personal information with personal information, the combined information will be treated as personal information for as long as it remains combined</p>
      <h2>5. USE OF PERSONAL INFORMATION </h2>
      <p>We will not rent, sell, or share Your personal information with any third-parties, except as specifically described herein.</p>
      <p>We will use personal information collected via Easy Snap App for the purposes of:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>a) providing and personalising the Services, monitoring usage of Easy Snap App;</li>
        <li>b) helping Us create, develop, operate, deliver, protect, promote and improve Our products, Services, content and advertising, to deliver personalized experiences and for loss prevention purposes. For example, so that Our Services work well for You, We offer tools that apply filters and video effects, that fit the contours of Your face, that modify the size and shape of facial features such as Your nose or eyes, or that follow facial movements in videos. In order to enable these Services, We use the information We have to distinguish patterns of shape and form that compose a digital image of a still or moving face. For the purposes of developing and improving Our products and Services, We may also make photo or video records of Your using the Services;</li>
        <li>c) dealing with Your enquiries and requests;</li>
        <li>d) analysing the video effects that are selected and how people share images or videos, such as from Easy Snap App to third-party services, or conducting surveys and researches, producing reports and statistics on the usage of Easy Snap App, testing features in development, and analysing the information We have to evaluate and improve products and Services, develop new products or features, and conduct audits and troubleshooting activities;</li>
        <li>e) sharing information with financial institutions, relevant authorities and/or any person or entity that has the legal right to such information, as well as verifying Your identity, if We suspect that You have engaged or attempted to engage in fraudulent, unlawful, dishonest or improper activity while using the Services;</li>
        <li>f) ensuring and protecting the safety and security of Easy Snap App; protecting the rights and property of Us, Our users or others; investigating, remedying or preventing potential or actual violations of this Privacy Policy and Our Terms and Conditions;</li>
        <li>g) detecting and resolving any fraud or security concerns arising out of or relating to the Services; </li>
        <li>h) being compliant with any valid legal process, governmental request, or applicable law, rule, or regulation, preventing unlawful, dishonest or improper activity;</li>
        <li>i) sharing information with Our legal advisors and insurers in case of legal disputes and claims; </li>
        <li>j) sharing information with third party service providers to the extent that it is reasonably necessary to perform, improve, promote, protect or maintain the the Services. For example, We may use third-party analytics tools to help Us measure use of Our Services, or We may use vendors that provide infrastructure services to help Us provide and maintain the Services.</li>
        <li>k) sending You messages about faults and service issues, keeping You up to date with news about Our software and products that You have purchased and/or other Easy Snap products and related information. For these purposes We may engage third party providers (e.g. those providing push notification services) and share the information collected via Easy Snap App with them.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Third party services providers with whom We share information under this Privacy Policy may use the information shared by Us for the purposes of targeting, interest-based advertising, conducting analytics or market research and other lawful purposes.</p>
      <p>We will ask for Your separate permissions to use Your camera and microphone, as well as for sending push notifications to You. If You change Your mind re permissions granted, You will be able to revoke them at any time afterwards by changing settings on Your Device. However, please note that rejecting or switching off these permissions shall negatively affect the use of Easy Snap App: Easy Snap App shall lose its full functionality</p>
      <h2>6. DISCLOSURE OF INFORMATION </h2>
      <p>We may disclose personal information if: (a) it is requested by any judicial, non-judicial state or supranational authority required by any applicable laws, regulation, edict, local acts; (b) it is shared under Section 5 of this Privacy Policy; (c) it is necessary for national security, law enforcement, or other issues of public importance that disclosure of information is necessary. We may also disclose personal information to companies within Our corporate group of companies.</p>
      <p>We may disclose personal information to successive operator of Easy Snap App solely for the purposes of providing You the Services. In the event that the ownership of Banuba (or any portion of Our assets) changes as a result of a merger, acquisition, division, separation, consolidation, transformation to another legal form, or in the event of bankruptcy, information We have, including information from or about You, may be transferred to another company.</p>
      <p>Hereby You give Us consent on Our usage and disclosure of personal information We collect, as stipulated in Sections 5 and 6 of the Privacy Policy. However, in order to disclose Your personal information to any third parties, in cases not indicated in the Policy, We will ask for Your prior consent.</p>
      <p>Where appropriate, before disclosing Your personal information to a third party, We shall contractually require the third party to take adequate precautions to protect that data and maintain confidentiality.</p>
      <h2>7. STORAGE OF INFORMATION</h2>
      <p>We are based Hong Kong and comply with the applicable data protection laws. </p>
      <p>We operate internationally and provide Our Services to Easy Snap App users worldwide allowing them to communicate with each other across the globe. That means that Your personal information may need to be transferred to, stored and processed in countries where data protection and privacy regulations may be different from Your home country and offer even lower level of protection. Personal information We collect from You may also be transferred to, stored and processed outside the European Economic Area. We limit such a transfer, storage and processing to the purposes specified in Sections 5 and 6. By using Our Services, You consent to this transfer, storage, and processing of personal information to and in the U.S., E.U. and other countries.</p>
      <p>The Easy Snap App servers that are used to store the information are owned and hosted by Amazon Web Services, LLC, an Amazon.com Company in USA and E.U. Regardless of where You use Our Services or otherwise provide information to Us, the information may be transferred to and maintained on servers located in the U.S., E.U. or any other country globally. </p>
      <p>We limit access to personal information We collect to employees who We believe reasonably need to come into contact with that information to provide Services to You or in order to fulfill their official duties. These employees are bound by confidentiality obligations and may be subject to liability, if they fail to meet these obligations. We will take all steps reasonably necessary to ensure that Your personal information is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</p>
      <p>We adopt appropriate data collection, storage and processing practices and security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure or destruction of information and data stored on Our servers.</p>
      <p>In case any of the collected data is considered as biometric identifier or biometric information or similar legal category, it will be permanently destroyed when the initial purpose for collecting or obtaining such identifiers or information has been satisfied or within 3 years of the individual’s last usage of the Services, whichever occurs first. In all other aspects this data, if any, will be treated similarly as personal data, unless qualified as non-personal information.</p>
      <p>We will retain Your personal information for a reasonable period necessary to fulfill the purposes for collecting it or as long as applicable law requires. </p>
      <h2>8.DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTY</h2>
      <p>Using the Internet to collect and process personal data necessarily involves the transmission of data on an international basis.  Therefore, by using the Services and communicating electronically with Us, You acknowledge and agree to Our processing of information in this way. Although We will do Our best to protect Your personal information, We cannot warrant the security of Your information transmitted via the Internet; any transmission is at Your own risk. Once We have received Your information, We will use strict procedures and security features to try to prevent unauthorised access. </p>
      <h2>9.CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY</h2>
      <p>Please note that this Privacy Policy may change from time to time. We will post the updated version of Privacy Policy on this page and any changes will become effective as of date of such post. You acknowledge and agree that it is Your responsibility to review this Privacy Policy periodically and become aware of amendments. Your continued use of the Services following the posting of changes to this Privacy Policy will be deemed Your acceptance of those changes.</p>
      <h2>10. QUESTIONS </h2>
      <p>If You have any requests concerning Your personal information or any queries with regard to this Privacy Policy please feel to contact through Our website <a href="https://www.banuba.com/" target="_blank">https://www.banuba.com/</a> or at <a href="mailto:https://www.banuba.com/"">hello@banuba.com</a></p>
      <h2>11. LANGUAGE</h2>
      <p>The English language version of this Privacy Policy shall be the prevailing version in the event of any discrepancy between any translated versions of this Privacy Policy.</p>
